                        <tr>
                            <td valign="top" class="content" bgcolor="#ffffff" style="padding: 22px 30px; color: #484569; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-size: 17px; line-height: 24px;">
                                <h2 style="color: #000; font-size: 24px; font-weight: bold; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; margin: 15px 0 0; line-height: 34px; padding-bottom: 8px;">News Picks</h2>		<div class="article-list" style="padding: 0; margin: 0;">
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://thetyee.ca/News/2024/05/07/BC-LNG-By-Rail-Risk/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">1. What would BC risk shipping LNG by rail?</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">An inland gas liquefaction facility proposed for north of Prince George could make Canada the first country in North America to make liquified natural gas a regular commodity on its rail lines and is raising concerns about safety.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>The Tyee</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/climate-lab/pse-may-turn-off-power-in-parts-of-wa-to-prevent-wildfires-this-year/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">2. PSE may turn off power in parts of WA to prevent wildfires</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">Puget Sound Energy, the state’s largest utility, is warning customers it could turn off power in some communities to prevent its power lines from sparking wildfires.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>The Seattle Times</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.theurbanist.org/2024/05/08/issaquah-approves-affordable-housing-incentives/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">3. Issaquah, WA, approves affordable housing incentives near future light rail</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">The Issaquah City Council this week voted to approve a tax exemption intended to spur the construction of denser mixed-use housing in its transit-rich central city, where the city’s planned light rail station is set to open sometime in the 2040s.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>The Urbanist</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.opb.org/article/2024/05/06/oregon-groundwater-declining/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">4. Radio: OR's groundwater is declining</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">Oregon’s groundwater is being used faster than it’s being replenished, and the state’s aquifers are declining. The Oregon Water Resources Department is proposing new rules in response.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>OPB</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://publicola.com/2024/05/07/burien-proposes-transitional-housing-ban-that-may-violate-state-law/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">5. Burien, WA, proposes transitional housing ban that may violate state law</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">The Burien City Council discussed legislation Monday night that would ban transitional housing, including tiny house villages, within 500 feet of any school, park, day care, playground, or recreational facility, but at the last minute decided to hold off on approving it until they can figure out whether state law prohibits their plan.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>PubliCola</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://thetyee.ca/Opinion/2024/05/07/Next-Big-Steps-Fix-Housing-Crisis/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">6. Here are the next big steps to fix BC's housing crisis</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">Private developers aren’t going to do it alone. We need an explosion in public and non-profit housing.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>The Tyee</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.capitolhillseattle.com/2024/05/seattle-boosts-transit-levy-proposal-to-1-45b-with-100m-more-for-sidewalks-bikes-and-transit/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">7. Seattle boosts transit levy proposal to $1.45B</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">Mayor Bruce Harrell’s office has finalized his proposal for the city’s next transportation levy planned to go before Seattle voters in November, now with an even bigger price tag: $1.45 billion.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>Capitol Hill Seattle Blog</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/07/podcasts/the-daily/ocean-temperature-climate.html?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">8. Podcast: Changing ocean temps could upend life on Earth</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">While many of the effects of climate change, including heat waves, droughts and wildfires, are already with us, some of the most alarming consequences are hiding beneath the surface of the ocean.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>The New York Times</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.theguardian.com/environment/article/2024/may/08/renewable-energy-passes-30-of-worlds-electricity-supply?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">9. Renewable energy passes 30% of world's electricity supply</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">Renewable energy accounted for more than 30 percent of the world’s electricity for the first time last year following a rapid rise in wind and solar power, according to new figures.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>The Guardian</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div style="padding: 0; margin: 0 0 25px;">
                                        <h3 class="post-title" style="margin: 0; line-height: 18px; padding-bottom: 5px;">
                                            <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #29473d; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 18px; font-weight: bold; display: inline-block; margin: 0 0 0;" href="https://www.desmog.com/2024/05/08/vaccine-for-climate-misinformation-disinformation/?utm_source=Sightline%20Institute&utm_medium=web-email&utm_campaign=Sightline%20News%20Selections" target="_blank">10. A vaccine for climate misinformation</a>
                                        </h3>
                                        <div class="post-excerpt" style="font-size: 17px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 21px; color: #414042;">Facts aren’t enough to combat false and misleading messaging. Experts suggest an additional strategy.</div>
                                        <div class="post-meta" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 17px; margin-top: 5px; color: #414042;"><em>DeSmog</em>, May 08</div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
